snippet: The dispute centered on a meeting held in Amman, the Jordanian capital, by 11 Iraqi Sunni groups, including some that are actively fighting the Iraqi government.
abstract: Five bombs explode in Baghdad, killing 30 people, as tensions continue between Iraq and Jordan over meeting held in Amman, Jordan, by Iraqi Sunni groups, including some that are actively fighting the Iraqi government; Jordanian government was not involved in the meeting, but Iraqis express anger that Jordan allowed the meeting to take place.
